Drop unused value labels

Source: R/drop_unused_value_labels.R
drop_unused_value_labels.Rd

Drop value labels associated to a value not present in the data.

Usage

drop_unused_value_labels(x)

Arguments

x

A vector or a data frame.

Examples

x <- labelled(c(1, 2, 2, 1), c(yes = 1, no = 2, maybe = 3))
x
#> <labelled<double>[4]>
#> [1] 1 2 2 1
#> 
#> Labels:
#>  value label
#>      1   yes
#>      2    no
#>      3 maybe
drop_unused_value_labels(x)
#> <labelled<double>[4]>
#> [1] 1 2 2 1
#> 
#> Labels:
#>  value label
#>      1   yes
#>      2    no
